# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored.

# Required: your Anthropic API key.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Optional: override the tool-author / agent model. Defaults to claude-sonnet-4-6.
#   FORGE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5   # the plan's original pin (legacy)
#   FORGE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8     # maximum synthesis quality
# FORGE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Optional: the test author is a SEPARATE, black-box adversarial agent.
# Defaults to FORGE_MODEL; point it at a different (stronger) model so the
# tester is independent of the builder — likelier to catch its bugs.
#   FORGE_TEST_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
# FORGE_TEST_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Optional: agent identity (1Password). When an identity is present, synthesized
# tools may declare the credentials they need BY REFERENCE (op://vault/item/field);
# the harness brokers them just-in-time at runtime and the value never enters the
# tool source, the model's context, or disk. Dormant without one — Forge runs as
# before. Two backends (the broker uses whichever is available):
#   - Service account (Business/Teams): a dedicated machine identity, the ideal.
#       OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN=ops_...
#   - User session (personal account): enable the 1Password desktop app's CLI
#       integration (Settings > Developer > Integrate with 1Password CLI), or run
#       `op account add`. The agent then acts under your unlocked session, still
#       scoped by the allowlist below. No token needed.
# Policy: reference prefixes the agent is allowed to request (comma-separated).
# Default-deny — an empty/absent allowlist grants nothing (zero standing privilege).
# Use your own vault's name, e.g. op://Private or op://Personal:
#   FORGE_OP_ALLOWED=op://Private
# Requires the 1Password CLI: brew install 1password-cli
